## version 0.22.0

- fix session cookies not persisted after 2FA trust step — subsequent commands no longer fail with "session expired" errors after authenticating (#133)
- the `install` command now checks for passwordless sudo before starting and tells you how to set it up if needed. No more silent hangs waiting for a password in unattended mode (#22)
- improve error reporting for AWS credential failures — xcodeinstall now detects your profile type (SSO, `aws login`, static credentials) and suggests the appropriate reauthentication command (#124)
- bump swift-srp to 2.3.0 (#131)
- bump swift-log to 1.12.0 (#130)
- bump swift-argument-parser to 1.7.1 (#128)
- bump swift-crypto to 4.5.0 (#127)
- bump Noora to 0.56.0 (#126)
- bump soto to 7.14.0 (#125)
- update Swift Docker tag to v6.3 (#129)
- consolidate test helper for temporary directory creation (#123)

## version 0.15

- add `--profile` (`-p`) option to specify an AWS profile name from `~/.aws/credentials` or `~/.aws/config`
- add support for `aws login` (SSO) style credentials in the credential provider chain
- automatically prompt and store Apple credentials in Secrets Manager when they don't exist yet (no need to run `storesecrets` first)
- improved error messages when AWS credentials are not found or profile name is invalid
- update README

## version 0.3

- Build scripts now produce a fat binary (multiple commits)
- Build scripts produce brew bottles (binaries) (multiple commits)
- Build scripts update brew formula (multiple commits)
- bump version to v0.3
- add initial version for build and release shell scripts ([#e84f9f6](https://github.com/sebsto/xcodeinstall/commit/e84f9f6a3ccd48e3850b925d2431aabf38030ad7))
- add AWS Secrets Manager support to `signout` command ([#6d6380f](https://github.com/sebsto/xcodeinstall/commit/6d6380f46c570bc1a4ff8950f972edb13c371f05))

